text: Cora is an unincorporated community in Lewis County, in the U.S. state of Washington. ==History== Cora was founded in 1886, and named after Cora Davis, a first settler. A post office was established at Cora in 1890, and remained in operation until 1908. ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in Lewis County, Washington Category:Unincorporated communities in Washington (state)
title: Cora, Washington
